<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-06-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-06-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">411.12/2331</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Boal</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 3652</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-05">June 5, 1936</date>.<lb/>[Received June
                                10.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to refer to the
                            Department’s instruction 1109 of May 29, 1936, regarding the procedure
                            for unmemorialized General Claims, and to report that on June 31 handed
                            to the Minister for Foreign Affairs our note 1634 dated June 2,
                            embodying the substance of this instruction. General Hay read the note
                            through and said that he would take it under consideration immediately
                            with a view to replying in ample time so that arrangements could be made
                            as desired by the Department before June 30.</p>
                        <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Pierre de L.
                            Boal</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>